Tom’s first day on the school bus | 汤姆在校车上的第一天
Tom and his mum stood at the school bus stop.| 汤姆和他的妈妈站在校车站台。
A small red bus stopped in front of them.| 一辆红色的小公共汽车停在他们前面。
The doors opened.| 门打开了。
‘Go on,’ Tom’s mum said.|“继续走，” 汤姆的妈妈说。
‘I don’t want to,’ Tom said.|“我不想，” 汤姆说。
‘But you have to!’ she said kindly|“但是你必须去！” 她和蔼地说
and gave him a little push.| 并且轻轻地推了他一下。
The big doors closed.| 大门关上了。
Tom didn’t believe what he saw.| 汤姆不相信他所看到的。
The bus was very big inside and | 公共汽车里面非常大，并且
it had blue walls with flowers on them.| 它有蓝色的墙壁，墙上有花。
There were lots of happy children sitting on the purple seats.| 有许多开心的孩子坐在紫色的座位上。
The friendly driver smiled.| 友好的司机笑了。
‘Good morning, Tom. Welcome.|“早上好，汤姆。欢迎。
I’m Brenda and this is your bus buddy, Bruno!’| 我是布伦达，这是你的校车伙伴，布鲁诺！”
‘Hi, Tom. This is your seat, next to mine,’ Bruno said.|“嗨，汤姆。这是你的座位，在我的旁边，” 布鲁诺说。
When Tom sat down, Brenda | 当汤姆坐下时，布伦达called,
‘Put on your seatbelts everyone, please!’| 喊道：“请大家系好安全带！”